### Event-aware Noise Initialization

During training, we construct the input latent by adding noise on the clean video latent. The noise schedule leaves some residual signal even at the terminal diffusion timestep \(T\). As a result, the diffusion model has a domain gap to generalize the video during the inference time when we sample from random Gaussian noise without any real data signal. To solve this train-test discrepancy problem, during the testing, we obtain the base noise by adding noise on event-accumulated frames using the forward process of DDPM . The noise latent for frame \(i\) can be expressed as:

